<div class="highlight views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first highlight-with-narrow3"><a class="feature-link" href="https://cigionline.org/internet-survey-2016"><div class="type">Perspective</div><h3>2016 CIGI-Ipsos Global Survey on Internet Security and Trust</h3><div class="short"><div class="feature-image"><img src=https://www.cigionline.org/sites/default/files/imagecache/feature_square/14464612731_07a5978e0b_o_1.jpg alt=""/></div>A new survey finds most global citizens favour enabling law enforcement to access private online conversations if they have valid national security reasons.</div></a></div><div class="top-row feature-block-row" data-columns="3"><div class="feature-block-cell views-row views-row-2 views-row-even narrow-with-highlight3"><a class="feature-link" href="/publications/capital-flows-emerging-market-economies-feast-or-famine-forever"><div class="type">CIGI Papers</div><h3>Capital Flows to Emerging Market Economies: Feast or Famine Forever?</h3><div class="short"><div class="feature-image"><img src="https://www.cigionline.org/sites/default/files/imagecache/user_square_thumb/shutterstock_263967125.jpg" alt="" title="" width="75" height="75" class="imagecache imagecache-user_square_thumb imagecache-default imagecache-user_square_thumb_default"/></div>What are the macroeconomic, macroprudential and financial policy measures that emerging market economies could implement in challenging global conditions?</div></a></div><div class="feature-block-cell views-row views-row-3 views-row-odd narrow-with-highlight3"><a class="feature-link" href="/publications/deeper-look-chinas-going-out-policy"><div class="type">CIGI Commentaries</div><h3>A Deeper Look at China’s “Going Out” Policy</h3><div class="short"><div class="feature-image"><img src="https://www.cigionline.org/sites/default/files/imagecache/user_square_thumb/8033512490_9b4392f2c0_o.jpg" alt="" title="" width="75" height="75" class="imagecache imagecache-user_square_thumb imagecache-default imagecache-user_square_thumb_default"/></div>China’s fast-growing outgoing FDI and aid, in particular, its grand strategy of OBOR, have generated great enthusiasm in China and serious concern elsewhere.</div></a></div><div class="feature-block-cell views-row views-row-4 views-row-even narrow-with-highlight3"><a class="feature-link" href="/publications/pragmatic-approach-right-be-forgotten"><div class="type">CIGI Papers</div><h3>A Pragmatic Approach to the Right to Be Forgotten</h3><div class="short"><div class="feature-image"><img src="https://www.cigionline.org/sites/default/files/imagecache/user_square_thumb/shutterstock_173593805.jpg" alt="" title="" width="75" height="75" class="imagecache imagecache-user_square_thumb imagecache-default imagecache-user_square_thumb_default"/></div>This paper considers the shape that a “right to be forgotten” is taking in the online world, in the aftermath of the Google Spain decision.</div></a></div></div><div class="bottom-row feature-block-row" data-columns="3"><div class="feature-block-cell views-row views-row-5 views-row-odd narrow-with-highlight3"><a class="feature-link" href="/blogs/asia-pacific-security/american-missile-defense-south-korea-boon-stability"><div class="type">blog</div><h3>American Missile Defense in South Korea: A Boon for Stability?</h3><div class="short"><div class="feature-image"><img src="https://www.cigionline.org/sites/default/files/imagecache/user_square_thumb/ap_9827851647021_0.jpg" alt="" title="" width="75" height="75" class="imagecache imagecache-user_square_thumb imagecache-default imagecache-user_square_thumb_default"/></div>The THAAD issue is morphing into a power game that could have repercussions on the US-China rivalry as well as China-South Korea ties.</div></a></div><div class="feature-block-cell views-row views-row-6 views-row-even narrow-with-highlight3"><a class="feature-link" href="/publications/growth-innovation-and-cop-21-case-new-investment-innovation-infrastructure"><div class="type">Policy Briefs</div><h3>Growth, Innovation and COP 21: The Case for New Investment In Innovation Infrastructure</h3><div class="short"><div class="feature-image"><img src="https://www.cigionline.org/sites/default/files/imagecache/user_square_thumb/train-retouched.jpg" alt="" title="" width="75" height="75" class="imagecache imagecache-user_square_thumb imagecache-default imagecache-user_square_thumb_default"/></div>First-generation energy innovation firms are ready to help Canada lower greenhouse gas emissions, but innovation in financing clean technology is required.</div></a></div><div class="feature-block-cell views-row views-row-7 views-row-odd views-row-last narrow-with-highlight3"><a class="feature-link" href="/videos/crisis-yemen-inside-issues-65"><div class="type">video</div><h3>Crisis in Yemen | Inside the Issues 6.5</h3><div class="short"><div class="feature-image"><img src="https://www.cigionline.org/sites/default/files/imagecache/user_square_thumb/shutterstock_249446422.jpg" alt="" title="" width="75" height="75" class="imagecache imagecache-user_square_thumb imagecache-default imagecache-user_square_thumb_default"/></div>In episode five of season six, CIGI Research Associate Jacqueline Lopour discusses Yemen&#039;s "forgotten war" and humanitarian crisis.</div></a></div></div></div> </div>
